1. Can we create object of an interface - No
2. Can we have constructors inside an interface - No
3. Can we have constructors inside an Abstract class - Yes
4. Can Abstract method of abstract class be final - No
5. Can abstract method be static - No
6. Can abstract methods be private - No
7. Can we create object of an Abstract class - No
8. Variables cannot be overridden
9. Can the abstract method of an interface be final, static or private - No
10.Interface can have concrete methods, provided that they are either static or have
   access modifier as default, so static abstract method is not allowed in an interface but static concrete method is allowed
11. static method of a class can be inherited and cannot be overridden BUT static method of an interface cannot be inherited and therefore obviously
    cannot be overridden
12. Default method on an interface can be both inherited and overridden and while doing overriding we need to
    replace default access modifier with any other access modifier